ting or wringing out of the ground, \"to pull up or extract\".\nUltimately, from Proto-Semitic *lapt-.\nCompare: Hebrew לֶפֶת (lefet, “turnip”), Classical Syriac ܠܰܦܬܳܐ (laftā, “turnip”), Akkadian 𒇻𒂠𒊬 (LU.UB₂.SAR /⁠laptu, liptu⁠/, “turnip”)."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n37855", "headword_ar": "لِفْتٌ", "root": "lft", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "half"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a thing; syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$q~N", "text_ar": "شقٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and its"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "side;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SigowN", "text_ar": "صِغْوٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, K;) i. e.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaAnibN", "text_ar": "جَانِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA talotafito lifota fulaAnK", "text_ar": "لَا تَلْتَفِتْ لِفْتَ فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Look not towards such a one."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A cow,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bull;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baqarapN", "text_ar": "بَقَرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.)       -A3-  A woman who is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stupid, foolish,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of little sense."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^alofatu", "text_ar": "اَلْفَتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".       -A4-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "vulva"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a lioness. (K.)       -A5-  [A name now given in Egypt to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Brassica napus"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of Linn.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a edulis;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Delile, Flor. Aeg., No. 597;) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rape;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "salojamN", "text_ar": "سَلْجَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[a name given in Egypt to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Brassica napus"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of Linn.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "β", "text_ar": "β", "orth_type": "plain"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "oleifera:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Delile, ubi supra, No. 598:)] (S, K:) Az. says, “ I have not heard it from any person confided in for accuracy, and know not whether it be Arabic or not: ” (TA:) Ibn-El-Kubbee asserts it to be a Nabathean word. (MF.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "K", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n37856", "headword_ar": "لَفَتٌ", "root": "lft", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having one of his horns twisted upon,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "over, the other."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "Said of a he-goat. (S.)"}], "source_refs": []}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}